## Layer Architecture

<!-- Define the dependency ordering within each domain -->
<!-- Layers can only import from layers to their LEFT -->

<!--
Example ordering:

  Types -> Config -> Repository -> Service -> Runtime -> UI

Rules:
- A layer may only import from layers to its LEFT in this chain.
- UI may NOT import from Repository directly.
- Service may NOT import from UI or Runtime.
- Cross-domain imports go through the Service layer (never Repository).
-->

| Layer | May Import From | Examples |
|-------|----------------|---------|
<!-- | Types | (none) | DTOs, enums, constants | -->
<!-- | Config | Types | Configuration classes, properties | -->
<!-- | Repository | Types, Config | Data access, JPA entities, QueryDSL | -->
<!-- | Service | Types, Config, Repository | Business logic, orchestration | -->
<!-- | Runtime | Types, Config, Service | Controllers, CLI, scheduled jobs | -->
<!-- | UI | Types, Config, Service | React components, pages | -->

